---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [{"href":"index.html","label":"Flagship"},{"href":"#angles","label":"All angles"},{"href":"#how","label":"How to use"}];
const navCta = {"href":"mailto:benoit@phidea.fr","label":"Email Benoit"};
---

<Layout variant="angles-index" noIndex>
  <Nav variant="angles-index" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">Internal · positioning tests</span>
    <h1>Six angles. <em>One company.</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Phidea is running six positioning tests in parallel on phidea.eu. Each has
      its own landing, its own primary CTA, its own intended persona. Point
      campaigns at different URLs and compare signup rates, demo requests, and
      message-to-message engagement.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="#angles" class="btn btn-primary">See the six angles →</a>
      <a href="index.html" class="btn btn-ghost">See the flagship</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="angles">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Live variants</div>
      <h2>Pick a starting point.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        All six pages share the same design system but differ on hook, hero,
        product emphasis, and CTA. Each form submission carries a
        <code>variant</code> hidden field so you can attribute in the CRM.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="angle-grid">

      <a class="angle-card" href="index.html">
        <div class="tag">Flagship · Observability</div>
        <h3>See every AI answer. Prove every regulation.</h3>
        <p>Observability / monitoring wedge. "Datadog for AI apps in regulated insurance." Synthetic buyers, live regulatory testing, session traces, cross-model funnel. Hero CTA: Request a demo.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="distribution.html">
        <div class="tag">Distribution</div>
        <h3>Be the insurance answer inside every AI agent.</h3>
        <p>Market-access / AI storefront wedge. For Head of Distribution at carriers. ChatGPT / Claude / Gemini / Perplexity visibility and governed storefronts. Hero CTA: Request a demo.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/distribution.html</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="evidence.html">
        <div class="tag">Evidence</div>
        <h3>Audit-ready AI. By default.</h3>
        <p>Compliance-first wedge. For Heads of Compliance, Legal, Risk. Policy-as-code, immutable ledger, one-click regulator bundles. Hero CTA: See a sample bundle.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/evidence.html</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="developers.html">
        <div class="tag">Developers</div>
        <h3>The governed MCP for insurance.</h3>
        <p>Technical / platform wedge. For CTOs and engineering leads. One MCP tool, policy packs, open reference agent (insurance-agent-v1). Hero CTA: Technical walkthrough.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/developers.html</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="synthetic.html">
        <div class="tag">Synthetic buyers</div>
        <h3>Let AI test your AI, 24/7.</h3>
        <p>Continuous red-teaming wedge — punchy, focused, standalone product. For Heads of AI who worry about model drift and launch-day QA rot. Hero CTA: See it probing.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/synthetic.html</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="presence-test.html">
        <div class="tag">Lead magnet · Free tool</div>
        <h3>Test your AI presence.</h3>
        <p>Top-of-funnel diagnostic. Free scorecard across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity. Converts curiosity into qualified leads. Hero CTA: Run the test.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/presence-test.html</div>
      </a>

      <a class="angle-card" href="newsletter.html">
        <div class="tag">Audience · Newsletter</div>
        <h3>AI in insurance, weekly.</h3>
        <p>Weekly newsletter. Lowest-commitment CTA (email only). Builds the audience you eventually sell to. Longest-horizon wedge. Hero CTA: Subscribe.</p>
        <div class="url">phidea.eu/newsletter.html</div>
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="how">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">How to use</div>
      <h2>What to test for, and in what order.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Running all six pages against the same cold traffic is noisy. Running
        each against the persona it was built for gives you signal.
      </p>
    </div>

    <table class="why-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Angle</th><th>Best audience to point at</th><th>Primary KPI</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Flagship (observability)</strong></td>
          <td class="w">Heads of AI at carriers, insurance CTOs, AI-ops leads</td>
          <td><strong>Demo request</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Distribution</strong></td>
          <td class="w">CMOs, Heads of Distribution, D2C carrier growth teams</td>
          <td><strong>Demo request</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Evidence</strong></td>
          <td class="w">Heads of Compliance, Legal, Risk at carriers</td>
          <td><strong>Sample bundle request</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Developers</strong></td>
          <td class="w">CTOs, platform leads, insurance engineering teams</td>
          <td><strong>Technical walkthrough</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Synthetic</strong></td>
          <td class="w">Heads of AI / AI-ops / QA at carriers with live AI</td>
          <td><strong>Demo request</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Presence Test</strong></td>
          <td class="w">Cold traffic — LinkedIn, Twitter, paid ads, general awareness</td>
          <td><strong>Scorecard signup (email)</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Newsletter</strong></td>
          <td class="w">Everyone else — content-driven social, SEO, referrals</td>
          <td><strong>Email subscription</strong></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div style="margin-top: 40px; padding: 24px 28px; background: var(--soft); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 14px;">
      <h3 style="font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 8px;">Running the test</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-2); font-size: 15px; margin: 0 0 8px;">
        Point a small LinkedIn or Reddit ad at each landing with persona-matched targeting. Spend $500 per variant over a week. Compare:
      </p>
      <ul style="color: var(--ink-2); font-size: 15px; margin: 0; padding-left: 20px;">
        <li>Conversion to primary CTA</li>
        <li>Share of traffic that clicks "All angles" to see the others</li>
        <li>Qualitative: what do reply emails say? What do they ask about?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
